t]], Canadian-American ice hockey player\n*  1941   &ndash; [[Alfred G. Gilman]], American pharmacologist and biochemist, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize]] laureate (d. 2015)\n*  1941   &ndash; [[Myron Scholes]], Canadian-American economist and academic, [[Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences|Nobel Prize]] laureate\n*  1941   &ndash; [[Twyla Tharp]], American dancer and choreographer\n*[[1942]] &ndash; [[Izzat Ibrahim al-Douri]], Iraqi field marshal and politician (d. 2015)\n*  1942   &ndash; [[Genevi\u00e8ve Bujold]], Canadian actress\n*  1942   &ndash; [[Andra\u00e9 Crouch]], American singer-songwriter, producer, and pastor (d. 2015)\n*  1942   &ndash; [[Julia Higgins]], English chemist and academic\n*[[1943]] &ndash; [[Philip Brunelle]], American conductor and organist\n*  1943   &ndash; [[Peeter Lepp]], Estonian politician, 37th [[Mayor of Tallinn]]\n*  1943   &ndash; [[Jeff Wayne]], American composer, musician, and lyricist\n*[[1945]] &ndash; [[Mike Burstyn]], American actor and singer\n*  1945   &ndash; [[Debbie Harry]], American singer-songwriter and actress \n*[[1946]] &ndash; [[Mick Aston]], English archaeologist and academic (d. 2013)\n*  1946   &ndash; [[Erkki Tuomioja]], Finnish sergeant and politician, [[Minister for Foreign Affairs (Finland)|Finnish Minister for Foreign Affairs]]\n*[[1947]] &ndash; [[Kazuyoshi Hoshino]], Japanese race car driver\n*  1947   &ndash; [[Malcolm Wicks]], English academic and politician (d. 2012)\n*[[1948]] &ndash; [[John Ford (musician)|John Ford]], English-American singer-songwriter and guitarist \n*[[1949]] &ndash; [[N\u00e9jia Ben Mabrouk]], Tunisian-Belgian director and screenwriter\n*  1949   &ndash; [[John Farnham]], English-Australian singer-songwriter \n*  1949   &ndash; [[David Hogan (composer)|David Hogan]], American composer and educator (d. 1996)\n*  1949   &ndash; [[Venkaiah Naidu]], Indian lawyer and politician \n*[[1950]] &ndash; [[David Duke]], American white supremacist, politician 