d: College Defensive Player of the Year \u2013 Past Recipients | publisher=Maxwell Football Club | accessdate=December 21, 2006 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090808003954/http://www.maxwellfootballclub.org/content/awards/bednarik/past_bednarik.htm | archivedate=August 8, 2009 }}</ref><br /><span style=\"font-weight:normal; font-size:.8em;\">''Best defensive player''</span>\n|-\n| '''2003''' || Teddy Lehman \u2013 ''LB''\n|}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n<!-- Column 4 -->\n{|\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#f2f2f2; font-size:1.1em;\" | [[Davey O'Brien Award]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.daveyobrien.com/Pages/Awards/pastQuarterAward.htm | title=Previous Davey O'Brien National Quarterback Award Winners | publisher=Davey O'Brien Foundation  | accessdate=December 21, 2006 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20061207225123/http://www.daveyobrien.com/Pages/Awards/pastQuarterAward.htm <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = December 7, 2006}}</ref><br /><span style=\"font-weight:normal; font-size:.8em;\">''Best quarterback''</span>\n|-\n| '''2003''' || Jason White\n|-\n| '''2004''' || Jason White\n|-\n| '''2008''' || Sam Bradford\n|-\n| '''2017''' || Baker Mayfield\n|-\n| '''2018''' || Kyler Murray\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#f2f2f2; font-size:1.1em;\" | [[Johnny Unitas Golden Arm Award]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.goldenarmfoundation.com/pastwinners.html | title=Past Winners | publisher=Johnny Unitas Golden Arm Educational Foundation  | accessdate=December 21, 2006 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20061218182923/http://www.goldenarmfoundation.com/pastwinners.html <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = December 18, 2006}}</ref><br /><span style=\"font-weight:normal; font-size:.8em;\">''Outstanding senior quarterback''</span>\n|-\n| '''2004''' || Jason White\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#f2f2f2; font-size:1.1em;\" | [[Burlsworth Trophy]]<br /><span style=\"font-weight:normal; font-size:.8em;\">''Most outstanding player who began his career as a walk-on''</span>\n|-\n| '''2015''' || Baker Mayfield \u2013 ''QB''\n|-\n| '''2016''' || Baker Mayfield \u2013 ''QB''\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#f2f2f2; font-size:1.1em;\" | [[Fred Biletnikoff Award]]<br /><span style=\"font-weight:normal; font-size:.8em;\">''Outstanding receiver''</span>\n|-\n| '''2016''' || [[Dede Westbrook]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#f2f2f2; font-size:1.1em;\" | [[John Mackey Award]]<br /><span style=\"font-weight:normal; font-size:.8em;\">''Most outstanding tight end''</span>\n|-\n|'''2017''' || [[Mark Andrews (American football)|Mark Andrews]]\n|}\n|}\n\n===All-Americans===\n[[File:Claude Reeds - OU 1st AA.jpg|thumb|Claude Reeds \u2013 Oklahoma's first All American.]]\n{{Main|List of Oklahoma Sooners football All-Americans}}\nEvery year, several publications release lists of their ideal \"team.\" The athletes on these lists are referred to as [[College Football All-America Team|All-Americans]]. The NCAA recognizes five All-American lists. They are the [[Associated Press]], [[American Football Coaches Association]], [[Football Writers Association of America]], [[The Sporting News]], and the [[Walter Camp Football Foundation]].<ref name=\"NCAA_AA\">{{cite web | title=2006 All-American Team announced | date=January 12, 2007 | accessdate=January 20, 2007 | publisher=NCAA.org | url=http://www.ncaasports.com/football/mens/story/9926097  }}</ref> Some of these also have levels such as a first team All-American, or second team, or third team. A consensus All-American is determined using a point system; three points if the player was selected for the first team, two points for the second team, and one point for the third team.<ref name=\"NCAA_AA\" /> Oklahoma has had 162 First Team All-Americans<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soonersports.com/sports/m-footbl/archive/m-footbl-all-americans.html |title=143 Oklahoma Football All-Americans |work=SoonerSports.com |publisher=[[University of Oklahoma]] |accessdate=August 31, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100628213711/http://www.soonersports.com/sports/m-footbl/archive/m-footbl-all-americans.html |archivedate=June 28, 2010 }}</ref> (80 consensus) in its history.\n\n===College Football Hall of Fame===\nOklahoma has 27 inductees in the [[College Football Hall of Fame]]. The first was coach [[Bennie Owen]] who was inducted as part of the inaugural class in 1951. The most recent is [[Rickey Dixon]] inducted in 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=College Football Hall of Fame|url=https://footballfoundation.org/hof_search.aspx|accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Oklahoma Sooners|Name|Position|Tenure|Inducted}}\n|- \n| {{sortname|Brian|Bosworth}} || [[Linebacker|LB]] || 1984\u20131986 || 2015\n|-\n| {{sortname|Tom|Brahaney}} || [[Center (gridiron football)|C]] || 1970\u20131972 || 2007\n|-\n| {{sortname|Kurt|Burris}} || [[Center (gridiron football)|C]] || 1951\u20131954 || 2000\n|-\n| {{sortname|Tony|Casillas}} || [[Defensive lineman|DL]] || 1982\u20131985 || 2004\n|-\n| {{sortname|Rickey|Dixon}} || [[Cornerback|CB]] || 1984\u20131987 || 2019\n|-\n| {{sortname|Forest|Geyer}} || [[Fullback (gridiron football)|FB]] || 1913\u20131915 || 1973\n|-\n| {{sortname|Keith|Jackson| Keith Jackson (tight end)}} || [[Tight End|TE]] || 1984\u20131987 || 2001\n|-\n| {{sortname|Biff|Jones}} || Coach || 1934\u20131936 ||1954\n|-\n| {{sortname|Tommy|McDonald|Tommy McDonald (American football)}} || [[Wide Receiver|WR]] || 1954\u20131956 || 1985\n|-\n| {{sortname|Bennie|Owen}} || Coach || 1905\u20131926 || 1951\n|-\n| {{sortname|Steve|Owens|Steve Owens (American football)}} || [[Running back|RB]] || 1967\u20131969 || 1991\n|-\n| {{sortname|Jim|Owens}} || [[Tight End|TE]] || 1946\u20131949 || 1982\n|-\n| {{sortname|Greg|Pruitt}} || [[Running back|RB]] || 1970\u20131972 ||1999\n|-\n| {{sortname|Claude|Reeds}} || [[Fullback (gridiron football)|FB]] || 1910\u20131912 || 1961\n|-\n| {{sortname|J. D.|Roberts}} || [[Offensive guard|OG]] || 1951\u20131953 || 1993\n|-\n| {{sortname|Rod|Shoate}} || [[Linebacker  LB]] || 1972\u20131974 || 2013\n|-\n| {{sortname|Barry|Switzer}} || Coach || 1973\u20131988 || 2001\n|-\n| {{sortname|Lee Roy|Selmon}} || [[Defensive end|DE]] || 1972\u20131975 || 1988\n|-\n| {{sortname|Billy|Sims}} || [[Running back|RB]] || 1975\u20131978 || 1995\n|-\n| {{sortname|Jim|Tatum}} || Coach || 1946 || 1984\n|-\n| {{sortname|Clendon|Thomas}} || [[Running back|RB]]/[[Defensive Back|DB]] || 1955\u20131957 ||2011\n|-\n| {{sortname|Jerry|Tubbs}} || [[Center (gridiron football)|C]]/[[Linebacker|LB]] || 1954\u20131956 || 1996\n|-\n| {{sortname|Billy|Vessels}} || [[Running back|RB]] || 1950\u20131952 || 1974\n|-\n| {{sortname|Jim|Weatherall}} || [[Offensive tackle|OT]] || 1949\u20131951 || 1992\n|-\n| {{sortname|Joe|Washington}} || [[Running back|RB]] || 1972\u20131975 || 2005\n|-\n| {{sortname|Bud|Wilkinson}} || Coach || 1947-1963 || 1969\n|-\n| {{sortname|Waddy|Young}} || End || 1936\u20131938 || 1986\n|}\n\n==Future non-conference opponents==\nAnnounced non-conference schedules as of December 27, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fbschedules.com/ncaa/oklahoma/ |title=Oklahoma Sooners Future Football Schedules |website=FBSchedules.com |access-date=December 27, 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:95%;\"\n|-style= \"text-align: center;\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Oklahoma Sooners|2020|2021|2022|2023|2024|2025}}\n|-<!-- First row -->\n| [[Missouri State Bears football|Missouri State]] (FCS)\n| at [[Tulane Green Wave football|Tulane]]\n| [[UTEP Miners football|UTEP]]\n| [[Illinois State Redbirds football|Illinois State]] (FCS)\n| [[Temple Owls football|Temple]]\n| [[Michigan Wolverines football|Michigan]]\n|-<!-- Second row -->\n| [[Tennessee Volunteers football|Tennessee]]\n| [[Western Carolina Catamounts football|Western Carolina]] (FCS)\n| at [[Nebraska Cornhuskers 