all team|2015]]\u2020 || Big Ten East || Urban Meyer || colspan=\"2\" | ''N/A lost tiebreaker to [[2015 Michigan State Spartans football team|Michigan State]]''\n|-\n| [[2016 Ohio State Buckeyes football team|2016]]\u2020 || Big Ten East || Urban Meyer || colspan=\"2\" | ''N/A lost tiebreaker to [[2016 Penn State Nittany Lions football team|Penn State]]''\n|-\n| [[2017 Ohio State Buckeyes football team|2017]] || Big Ten East || Urban Meyer || [[2017 Wisconsin Badgers football team|Wisconsin]] || '''W''' 27\u201321\n|-\n| [[2018 Ohio State Buckeyes football team|2018]]\u2020 || Big Ten East || Urban Meyer || [[2018 Northwestern Wildcats football team|Northwestern]] || '''W''' 45\u201324\n|-\n| [[2019 Ohio State Buckeyes football team|2019]] || Big Ten East || [[Ryan Day (American football)|Ryan Day]] || [[2019 Wisconsin Badgers football team|Wisconsin]] || '''W''' 34\u201321\n|}\n\u2020 Co-champions\n\n==Bowl games==\nOhio State has appeared in 51 bowl games earning a 25\u201326 record through the 2019 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/ohio-state/|title=Ohio State Buckeyes Bowls|website=College Football at Sports-Reference.com}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Ohio State Buckeyes|Season|Coach|Bowl|Opponent|Result}}\n|-\n| [[1920 Ohio State Buckeyes football team|1920]] || [[John Wilce]] || [[1921 Rose Bowl|Rose Bowl]] || [[California Golden Bears football|California]] || L 0\u201328 \n|-\n| [[1949 Ohio State Buckeyes football team|1949]] || [[Wes Fesler]] || [[1950 Rose Bowl|Rose Bowl]] || [[California Golden Bears football|California]] || '''W''' 17\u201314\n|-\n| [[1954 Ohio State Buckeyes football team|1954]] || [[Woody Hayes]] || [[1955 Rose Bowl|Rose Bowl]] || [[USC Trojans football|USC]] || '''W''' 20\u20137 \n|-\n| [[1957 Ohio State Buckeyes football team|1957]] || Woody Hayes || [[1958 Rose Bowl|Rose Bowl]] || [[Oregon Ducks football|Oregon]] || '''W''' 10\u20137 \n|-\n|-\n| [[1968 Ohio Stat